The Hanover Insurance Group Inc

Bartolome Carpio |
Domingo, Julio 23, 2017







Geode Capital Management LLC owned approximately 0.79% of The Hanover Insurance Group worth $30,120,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC.Accern also gave media coverage about the insurance provider an impact score of 56 out of 100, indicating that recent press coverage is somewhat likely to have an effect on the company's share price in the near future. (THG) Ex-Dividend Date Scheduled for June 07 ..." published on June 06, 2017 as well as Forbes.com's news article titled: "Hanover Insurance Group Becomes Oversold" with publication date: "September 08, 2016. Macquarie Group Ltd. now owns 369,319 shares of the insurance provider's stock valued at $33,261,000 after buying an additional 348,919 shares in the last quarter.
10/24/2016 - The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at Sandler O'Neill. Envestnet Asset Management Inc. now owns 2,557 shares of the insurance provider's stock worth $231,000 after buying an additional 89 shares in the last quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC raised its position in The Hanover Insurance Group by 1.5% in the fourth quarter. The firm owned 8,600 shares of the insurance provider's stock after buying an additional 800 shares during the period. The correct version of this news story can be accessed at https://www.thestockobserver.com/2017/07/22/teachers-retirement-system-of-the-state-of-kentucky-sells-960-shares-of-the-hanover-insurance-group-inc-nysethg.html. (THG) opened at 92.41 on Friday. The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc.The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 87.57 and a 200 day moving average of 87.43. The firm has a market cap of $3.93 billion, a PE ratio of 32.60 and a beta of 1.13.The value of the company's investment in Hanover Insurance Group Inc went from $2,990,000 to $2,706,000 a change of $284,000 quarter over quarter. Analysts forecast EPS of $1.47, up exactly $0.23 or 18.55 % from 2014's $1.24 EPS. The business had revenue of $1.19 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.22 billion. The Hanover Insurance Group had a net margin of 2.45% and a return on equity of 5.20%. The Hanover Insurance Group's revenue for the quarter was up 3.7% compared to the same quarter a year ago. During the same period in the previous year, the business posted $1.64 EPS. On average, equities research analysts anticipate that The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc. will post $5.99 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 9th were paid a $0.50 dividend. This represents a $2.00 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 2.16%. The Hanover Insurance Group's dividend payout ratio (DPR) is now 70.42%.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: "The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc". Finally, BidaskClub upgraded The Hanover Insurance Group from a "strong sell" rating to a "sell" rating in a research note on Saturday, June 10th. If you are viewing this report on another site, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of United States and worldwide trademark & copyright laws.Geode Capital Management LLC raised its stake in The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc.THG has been the subject of several recent research reports.Among 5 analysts covering Hanover Insurance Group (NYSE:THG), 2 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 2 Hold. Finally, Keefe, Bruyette & Woods restated a "sell" rating and set a $81.00 price objective on shares of The Hanover Insurance Group in a report on Friday, May 5th. The Hanover Insurance Group presently has an average rating of "Buy" and an average target price of $91.20. Three investment analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and three have issued a buy rating to the company. The company now has an average rating of "Buy" and an average target price of $91.20.The Company is involved in providing property and casualty insurance products and services. The Firm is engaged in providing property and casualty insurance services and products. The Company has four segments: Commercial Lines, Personal Lines, Chaucer and Other.




