Hanover Insurance Group Inc (NYSE:THG) Traded 6.5% Above Its 50 Day Moving Average 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsHanover Insurance Group Inc (NYSE:THG) Traded 6.5% Above Its 50 Day Moving Average
July 26, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



The stock last traded at $93.88 just a bit higher than the 50 day moving average of $88.12 and slightly over the 200 day moving average of $87.44.  The 50 day moving average moved up $5.76 and the 200 day average moved up $6.44.  (NYSE:THG) shares saw light trading volume with 6,404 shares changing hands in the last trading session.  Volume was down 97.82% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (THG).   As of quarter end Breton Hill Capital Ltd. had disposed of  a total of 944 shares trimming its stake by 12.0%. The value of the total investment in Hanover Insurance Group Inc went from $710,000 to $615,000 a change of $95,000 for the reporting period. As of the end of the quarter Oakbrook Investments LLC had sold 20 shares trimming its position 0.6%. The value of the investment in Hanover Insurance Group Inc decreased from $322,000 to $315,000 a change of 2.2% quarter to quarter.
 Mu Investments Co., Ltd. trimmed its position by shedding 120 shares a decrease of 24.0%. Mu Investments Co., Ltd. now holds 380 shares valued at $34,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 24.4%. Aperio Group, LLC bolstered its holdings by buying 387 shares an increase of 1.6% in the quarter. Aperio Group, LLC now controls 23,908 shares worth $2,119,000. The value of the position overall is up by 0.0%.
  On May 18 the company was changed to a “Market Perform” according to a Keefe Bruyette & Woods report a boost from the previous “Underperform” rating. On October 24, 2016 Sandler O'Neill added the stock to its research portfolio by announcing an initial rating of “Buy”.        Advertisement






 BMO Capital upgraded the stock and raised the price target  on March 28 changing the price objective from $86.00 to $98.00 and moving the rating from “Market Perform” to “Outperform”. On March 28 the stock rating was upgraded to “Outperform” from “Market Perform” with a current price target of $98.00 by analysts at BMO Capital.
 On November 12 the company was downgraded from “Overweight” to “Neutral” in a report issued by Piper Jaffray. On July 20 JMP Securities kept the stock rating at “Market Outperform” but raised the price target from $78.00 to $85.00.
 In the market the company is trading up by 1.59% since yesterday’s close of $92.41.  The company also announced a dividend paid on Friday June 30th, 2017.  The dividend payment was $0.500 per share for the quarter or $2.00 on an annualized basis.  This dividend represents a yield of $2.16.  The ex-dividend date was Wednesday the 7th of June 2017. 
 The most current P/E ratio is 33.11 and market capitalization is 3.99B.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $2.84 and is projected to be $5.99 for the current year with 42,538,000 shares outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $1.56 with next year’s EPS projected to be $7.06. 
 The Hanover Insurance Group, Inc., launched on January 12, 1995, is a holding company. The Company is involved in providing property and casualty insurance products and services. The Company has four segments: Commercial Lines, Personal Lines, Chaucer and Other. The Company markets its domestic products and services through independent agents and brokers in the United States, and conducts business internationally through a subsidiary, Chaucer Holdings Limited, which operates through the Society and Corporation of Lloyd’s (Lloyd’s)..
